{"lemma": "مِجَسٌّ", "slug": "مِجَسٌّ", "root": "ج.س.س", "root_slug": "ج-س-س", "root_link": "/words/roots/ج-س-س", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 3, "pos_tags": ["noun", "verb"], "has_etymology": true, "sense_count": 3}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n5773"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D8%AC%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%8C%D9%91"}}, "translations": {"en": "place for tactile judgment", "fa": "جای لمس برای قضاوت", "ur": "جگہ جس سے فیصلہ کیا جائے", "tr": "hissedilerek yargılanan yer", "id": "tempat untuk penilaian sentuh", "bn": "স্পর্শ করে বিচারের স্থান", "es": "lugar para juicio táctil", "fr": "lieu de jugement tactile", "de": "Ort zur taktile Beurteilung", "ru": "место для тактильной оценки", "zh": "用于触觉判断的地方"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "noun", "gloss": "place which one touches to make a judgment from it"}, {"pos": "noun", "gloss": "sensor, probe"}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to Zoroastrianize, to teach someone Zoroastrianism", "examples": [{"text": "كُلُّ مَوْلُودٍ يُولَدُ عَلَى الْفِطْرَةِ، فَأَبَوَاهُ يُهَوِّدَانِهِ أَوْ يُنَصِّرَانِهِ أَوْ يُمَجِّسَانِهِ", "english": "Every newborn is born upon the fitra; its parents then Judaize or Christianize or Zoroastrianize it."}]}]}, "etymology": {"source": "wiktextract", "text": "Noun of place from the root ج س س (j s s).\n\nTool noun from the root ج س س (j s s).\n\nDenominal verb of مَجُوس (majūs, “Zoroastrians”, collective), forming the root م ج س (m j s)."}, "ipa": ["/ma.d͡ʒass/", "/mi.d͡ʒass/", "/mad͡ʒ.d͡ʒa.sa/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n5773", "headword_ar": "مَجَسٌّ", "root": "js", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "(A, TA) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "majas~apN", "text_ar": "مَجَسَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, A, Mgh, Msb, K) The"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "place which one feels with his hand,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A,* Mgh, K, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "for the purpose of testing it, that he may form a judgment of it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh:) and ↓ the latter, the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "place which the physician feels [to know if a patient be hot or cold]:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb:) pl."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "majaAs~u", "text_ar": "مَجَاسُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, A, Msb, K.) You say, ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "majas~atuhu", "text_ar": "مَجَسَّتُهُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HaAr~apN", "text_ar": "حَارَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "[The place in which one feels him is hot]."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "kayofa taraY majas~ahaA", "text_ar": "كَيْفَ تَرَى مَجَسَّهَا"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "[How dost thou find the place in which one feels her?];"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "referring to a sheep or goat; to which one answers, \"Indicative of fatness.\" (A.) ―         -b2- [Hence, (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Anything external which indicates the internal condition."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] It is said in a prov., (S, A, Msb, K,) relating to camels, (Msb,)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^afowaAhuhaA majaAs~uhaA", "text_ar": "اَفْوَاهُهَا مَجَاسُّهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, A, K,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "majaAs~uhaA A^afowaAhuhaA", "text_ar": "مَجَاسُّهَا اَفْوَاهُهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHonaAkuhaA majaAs~uhaA", "text_ar": "اَحْنَاكُهَا مَجَاسُّهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (A, K,) (assumed tropical:) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Their mouths, or their palates, are the things which indicate their internal condition:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] for if they eat well, he who looks at them sufficiently knows their fatness, (S, Msb, K,) without feeling them: (S, K:) if one see them eat well, it is as though he felt them: (A, TA:) or, accord. to AZ, they feel the herbage, to test it, with their heads [or mouths] and their palates: so that, accord. to his explanation, the term"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mjAs~", "text_ar": "مجاسّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is tropically applied to these parts. (TA.) The prov. relates to external evidences of things explaining their internal qualities. (K) [And hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raEati AlA_ibilu AlkalaA^a bimajaAs~ihaA", "text_ar": "رَعَتِ الاـِبِلُ الكَلَاَ بِمَجَاسِّهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K) (tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The camels cropped the herbage with their mouths."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.)―         -b3-  You say also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fulaAnN waAsiEu Almajas~i", "text_ar": "فُلَانٌ وَاسِعُ المَجَسِّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like as you say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raHobu Al*~iraAEi", "text_ar": "رَحْبُ الذِّرَاعِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:) [app. meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Such a one is liberal, munificent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "generous"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: and in the contrary case,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Day~iqu Almajas~i", "text_ar": "ضَيِّقُ المَجَسِّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (A,) or ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Almajas~api", "text_ar": "المَجَسَّةِ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) or both, (TA,) signifying"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "gayoru raHobi AlS~adori", "text_ar": "غَيْرُ رَحْبِ الصَّدْرِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:) [app.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "not liberal"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; (K, TA;) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "not"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAsiEu Als~arobi", "text_ar": "وَاسِعُ السَّرْبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[which is explained as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of ample bosom,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "judgment,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "love;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of ample way,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "course of proceeding:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "but I rather incline to think that the right reading is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "waAsiEu Als~irobi", "text_ar": "وَاسِعُ السِّرْبِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and the meaning,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of ample,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "large, mind,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "heart"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) You also say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "laDiyqFA", "text_ar": "لَضِيقًا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A_in~a fiY majas~atika", "text_ar": "اـِنَّ فِى مَجَسَّتِكَ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(A) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "majas~ika", "text_ar": "مَجَسِّكَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA) (tropical:) [app,."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Verily in thy bosom,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mind,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "heart, is narrowness;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "in thee is illiberality."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}], "source_refs": ["A", "TA", "S", "Mgh", "Msb", "K"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}